latestIgtvVideos.caption:
This month at @_xtant_ Mallorca '22, I will be presenting my first film, #TheTurbanWeaversofBhujodi . This labour of love has been in the making for nearly four years now, four fleeting years that have been filled with nothing but gratitude and joy for the many interactions I have had with #ShamjiBhai. Filming him in his most sacred work spaces, at the loom, amidst reared sheep and spun yarn - taught me more about this indigenous art of turban weaving than any text ever. As I prepare to showcase and share thia experience with the world, I would also like to thank @chinar_farooqui of @injiri for giving me the opportunity to embark on this journey - who knew three years back that what began as a look book shoot would eventually pave the path for my first film. Life has strange ways of coming full circle. See you in Spain!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Iconic New York Illuminated Video
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Imagine a shimmering Klimt-like homage to New York at night!

Rendered in radiant gold and silver foils and luminous metallic inks, Iconic New York Illuminated© celebrates the lights and landmarks of New York at night. Masterfully printed and stamped on velvety black premium paper, this poster shines as brightly as the City itself after dark. “Everybody loves New York,” says designer Rafael Esquer. “I wanted to create a deluxe, collectible souvenir that says, New York loves you back—especially after dark.” Iconic New York Illuminated© is composed of more than 600 icons. Compared to the original 2013 Iconic New York© poster, this night edition has nearly 200 additional icons, including 28 buildings, 23 celebrities, 20 media outlets, 12 cultural institutions, 11 urban legends, 10 writers, 8 sports teams, 3 superheroes, and 1 saint.

Studio: @alfalfanewyork

Video : @gourabganguli
Calligraphy in Video : @minalnairi

latestIgtvVideos.title: PhulMala by @Chottogolpo
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Running and whirling through the phul mandis, 
Amidst the scads of marigolds and hibiscus,
Picking up the best flower as a token of love for their God,
Stopping by the temples, 
Smelling the fragrant agarbatties, 
Listening to the Panditji ringing the bells that peal across the skies,
Chotto Golpo plunges deep into the true moods and colours of Festive India
With a collection inspired by these joyous flowers: PHULMALA  by @chottogolpo

latestPosts.caption:
When I first met sisters Kamala and Jahnavi ( @samadhi.collective ), I was struck by the quiet serenity that surrounds them. Born into a life steeped in Vedanta, their path was shaped by parents who walked it before them as their own lives unfolded in rhythm with mantra, sacred texts, and deep-rooted tradition. Today, through the soulful space of Samādhi Collective, they share ancient wisdom as daily practice — not performance. Their teachings, music, and art are living expressions of peace. 

This is more than study. It is remembering.
This is more than practice. It is presence.
It is Samādhi.

Text: @anwesh_writes

latestPosts.caption:
A quiet pull, not a plan — that’s how #CalcuttaHouses began. Born from film-camera strolls and fading facades, founder Manish Golder and two fellow photographers felt the urgency: to capture the soul of a city before it vanished, one old house at a time. Not nostalgia, but honesty. Not ruins, but stories — layered, cracked, still standing.

Instagram became the archive: discreet, immediate, and unexpectedly powerful. Over 12 years later, homes have vanished, but the portraits remain—of architecture, of memory, of meaning. What started as three friends walking with wonder is now a well of tales - waiting to whisper back.

In frame: Manish Golder 
Image: gourab ganguli @gourabganguli 
Images of Kolkata: Calcutta Houses @calcuttahouses 
Text: Anwesh Bannerjee @anwesh_writes 

Manish is in Charu’s Theme kurta set 002
